\cf2\b\fs32 **(27) How do I read the blocked traffic log?**\cf0\b0\fs22\par
\par
The columns have the following meaning:\par
\par
1. Time (tap on a log entry to see the date)\par
1. Application icon (tap on a log entry to see the application name)\par
1. Application UID\par
1. Wi-Fi / mobile connection, green=allowed, red=blocked\par
1. Interactive state (screen on or off)\par
1. Protocol (see below) and packet flags (see below)\par
1. Source and destination port (tap on a log entry to lookup a destination port)\par
1. Source and destination IPv4 or IPv6 address (tap on a log entry to lookup a destination IP address)\par
1. Organization name owning the IP address (need to be enabled through the menu)\par
\par
Protocols:\par
\par
* ICMP\par
* IGMP\par
* ESP (IPSec)\par
* TCP\par
* UDP\par
* Number = one of the protocols in [this list](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_IP_protocol_numbers)\par
* 4 = IPv4\par
* 6 = IPv6\par
\par
Packet flags:\par
\par
* S = SYN\par
* A = ACK\par
* P = PSH\par
* F = FIN\par
* R = RST\par
\par
For a detailed explanation see [here](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transmission_Control_Protocol).\par
\par
